@startuml
title game-lib collision: dispatch architecture

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
hide empty members
hide circle

package "Construction / policy" {
  class CollisionBuilder <<builder>> {
    +build(options)
    +withCollision(...)
    +bodyDesc(...)
    +collider(...)
    +getOrCreateCollisionGroupId(type)
    +createCollisionFilter(allowedTypes)
  }

  class CollisionOptions <<type>>
  class CollisionComponent <<value>>
  class CollisionSelector <<type>>
  class CollisionMask <<enum>>
  class "matchesCollisionSelector(...)" as MatchSelector <<utility>>
}

package "Entity layer" {
  class GameEntity <<entity>> {
    +bodyDesc
    +colliderDesc
    +colliderDescs
    +body
    +colliders
    --
    +onCollision(selector, callback, phase, cooldown)
    +_collision(other, event)
  }

  interface CollisionHandlerDelegate <<delegate>> {
    +handleIntersectionEvent(event)
    +handlePostCollision(event)
  }

  class ZylemZone <<entity>> {
    +onEnter(callback)
    +onHeld(callback)
    +onExit(callback)
  }
}

package "Stage integration" {
  class StageEntityDelegate <<runtime>> {
    +spawn(entity)
    +attachPhysics(entity)
    +remove(entity)
  }
}

package "Physics runtime" {
  class ZylemWorld <<runtime>> {
    +attach(entity)
    +update(delta)
    +dispatch collisions
  }

  class RigidBodyDesc <<rapier>>
  class ColliderDesc <<rapier>>
  class RigidBody <<rapier>>
  class Collider <<rapier>>
  class "Rapier World" as RapierWorld <<external>>
}

ZylemZone --|> GameEntity
ZylemZone ..|> CollisionHandlerDelegate

CollisionBuilder --> CollisionOptions : reads
CollisionBuilder --> CollisionComponent : build()
CollisionBuilder --> RigidBodyDesc : bodyDesc()
CollisionBuilder --> ColliderDesc : collider()
CollisionBuilder --> CollisionMask : group ids / filters

MatchSelector --> CollisionSelector
MatchSelector --> CollisionMask

GameEntity o-- RigidBodyDesc : planned body
GameEntity o-- ColliderDesc : planned collider(s)
GameEntity o-- RigidBody : attached body
GameEntity o-- Collider : attached collider(s)
GameEntity ..> MatchSelector : filters callback targets

StageEntityDelegate --> GameEntity : spawn / track
StageEntityDelegate --> ZylemWorld : attach into world
StageEntityDelegate --> RigidBodyDesc : consumes
StageEntityDelegate --> ColliderDesc : consumes

ZylemWorld *-- RapierWorld : owns
ZylemWorld --> RigidBody : creates / updates
ZylemWorld --> Collider : creates / updates
ZylemWorld --> GameEntity : body refs + callback dispatch
ZylemWorld --> CollisionHandlerDelegate : delegate dispatch

note top of CollisionBuilder
CollisionBuilder is the low-level collision descriptor factory.

It is responsible for:
- body/collider descriptor creation
- collision group ID allocation
- allowed-type filter generation
- reusable collision policy helpers
end note

note right of StageEntityDelegate
StageEntityDelegate bridges author-created entities
into the live physics runtime.

Typical responsibilities:
- read entity body/collider descriptors
- create live Rapier objects through ZylemWorld
- store the resulting body/collider refs on the entity
end note

note bottom of ZylemWorld
Collision flow

1. Physics step runs in the world
2. Contacts / intersections are detected
3. ZylemWorld dispatches through two paths

Path A: entity callback path
- GameEntity.onCollision(...) registers callbacks
- ZylemWorld calls GameEntity._collision(...)
- selector matching + cooldown/phase logic decide delivery

Path B: delegate path
- entities implementing CollisionHandlerDelegate
  receive intersection and post-collision events directly
- useful for stateful sensors and zone-style entities
end note

note right of GameEntity
GameEntity is the common collision consumer.

It can participate in collision handling by:
- owning body/collider descriptors
- receiving live body/collider refs
- exposing onCollision(...) for filtered callbacks
end note

note right of ZylemZone
ZylemZone is the clearest example of the delegate path.

It behaves more like a stateful sensor than a simple
one-shot callback target, so it implements
CollisionHandlerDelegate and tracks enter/held/exit semantics.
end note

legend left
|= Path |= Purpose |
| Descriptor creation | CollisionBuilder creates body/collider descriptors and filter policy |
| Runtime attachment | StageEntityDelegate attaches entity physics into ZylemWorld |
| Callback dispatch | ZylemWorld -> GameEntity._collision(...) |
| Delegate dispatch | ZylemWorld -> CollisionHandlerDelegate |
endlegend

@enduml
